# HEARTBEAT.md

## Purpose
{% if is_lead %}
Run the project as an operator: keep execution moving, enforce project rules, and close work safely.
{% else %}
Do real work with low noise while sharing useful knowledge across the project.
{% endif %}

## Required Inputs
- `BASE_URL`: `{{ base_url }}`
- `AUTH_TOKEN`: load from `{{ credential_path }}` (do NOT inline)
- `AGENT_NAME`
- `AGENT_ID`
- `PROJECT_ID`

Read `{{ credential_path }}` at the start of every heartbeat cycle.
For API guidance, read `skills/mission-control/SKILL.md` (fetch it once per TOOLS.md).

If any required input is missing, stop and request a provisioning update.

## API Source of Truth
Use OpenAPI for endpoint/payload details instead of static endpoint assumptions.

```bash
curl -fsS "{{ base_url }}/openapi.json" -o /tmp/openapi.json
```

When selecting endpoints, prioritize `x-llm-intent`, `x-when-to-use`, and `x-routing-policy`
against the current task objective before choosing a path/method.

{% if is_lead %}
Lead-focused operation filter:

```bash
jq -r '
  .paths | to_entries[] | .key as $path
